blueprint.label: SpaceLaunch System
blueprint.description:
DO NOT ROTATE!  Though the Space Elevator will move, it will not rotate and thus connections to it will be broken.

Manually place the elevator after normal construction is started.  Change it's name from the planet's name (e.g. "Nauvis") to "Elevator".  Set electricity transfer direction to "up".

Build the "orbit" side while construction and cable manufacturing happens.

Set all trains to "automatic".

Finally, connect red & green wires from elevator to both big power poles near it.
